@startuml CodeReviewAutomationAssistant
left to right direction
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam actorStyle awesome

' ============ LEVEL 1: PRIMARY ACTORS (LEFT) ============
actor "Developer" as Developer
actor "Repository Admin" as Admin

note top of Developer
    **Primary Actor:** A software developer who submits pull requests 
    for code review and reviews automated feedback 
    to improve code quality and ensure adherence 
    to project standards.
end note

note top of Admin
    **Primary Actor:** A repository administrator or team lead 
    who configures the code review system, 
    sets quality rules and standards, 
    and monitors overall project code quality.
end note

' ============ LEVEL 2: USE CASES (CENTER) ============
rectangle "Code Review Automation Assistant System" {
    usecase "View Dashboard" as UC1
    usecase "View Review Comments" as UC2
    usecase "Submit Pull Request" as UC3
    usecase "Connect Repository" as UC4
    usecase "Generate Report" as UC5
    usecase "Configure Rules" as UC6
    
    ' Force internal vertical ordering
    UC1 -[hidden]right-> UC2
    UC2 -[hidden]right-> UC3
    UC3 -[hidden]right-> UC4
    UC4 -[hidden]right-> UC5
    UC5 -[hidden]right-> UC6
}

' ============ LEVEL 4: GITHUB ACTOR (RIGHT) ============
actor "GitHub" as System

' ============ LEVEL 5: GITHUB NOTE ============
note bottom of System
    **Secondary Actor:** External GitHub system that provides 
    webhook notifications, pull request data, 
    code content, and receives comments 
    to be posted back on pull requests.
end note

' ============ CONNECTIONS ============
Developer --> UC1
Developer --> UC2
Developer --> UC3
Admin --> UC4
Admin --> UC5
Admin --> UC6

' Keep System on the RIGHT (Level 4) using reverse arrow
UC3 --> System : webhook trigger
UC3 -[hidden]right-> System

' ============ LEVEL 3: USE CASE NOTES (SOLID LINES) ============
' To get solid lines, we define the note separately and link with --

note "**View Dashboard:** Developer or Repository Admin views \nthe code quality dashboard displaying metrics, \ntrends, repository statistics, pull request \nanalysis results, and quality scores to track \nproject health over time." as N1
UC1 -- N1

note "**View Review Comments:** Developer views automated review comments \ngenerated by the code review system \non their pull request, including identified \nissues, suggestions for fixes, severity levels, \nand code quality metrics." as N2
UC2 -- N2

note "**Submit Pull Request:** Developer submits a pull request \ncontaining code changes to the repository. \nGitHub system triggers the code review \nautomation system to analyze the changes \nand provide automated code review feedback." as N3
UC3 -- N3

note "**Connect Repository:** Repository Admin connects the code review \nsystem to a GitHub repository, authenticates \nwith GitHub API, and establishes webhook \nintegration to receive pull request \nnotifications." as N4
UC4 -- N4

note "**Generate Report:** System generates comprehensive quality reports \nafter analyzing pull requests containing \ndetailed findings, metrics, identified issues, \ncode complexity analysis, and improvement \nrecommendations." as N5
UC5 -- N5

note "**Configure Rules:** Repository Admin configures & customizes \ncode review rules including which static \nanalysis checks to run, severity levels, \nthresholds, code style guides, and quality \ngates required for PR approval." as N6
UC6 -- N6

@enduml